1: Update System and Install Java

sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y
java -version

2.Jenkins Installation on Ubuntu (Latest Method)

https://pkg.jenkins.io/

3: Start and Enable Jenkins
sudo systemctl start jenkins
sudo systemctl enable jenkins
sudo systemctl status jenkins  

4: Get Jenkins Admin Password
sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword


5: Access Jenkins Web Interface

first allow custom tcp port 8080 by selecting anywhere with ipv4 with all zeros in security grops of that instance 
http://your-server-ip(public-ip):8080

0d740e938eef4641b36cd509577aabfe

6.next install maven

wget https://archive.apache.org/dist/maven/maven-3/3.9.6/binaries/apache-maven-3.9.6-bin.tar.gz
sudo tar -xvzf apache-maven-3.9.6-bin.tar.gz -C /opt/
echo &#39;export PATH=/opt/apache-maven-3.9.6/bin:$PATH&#39; | sudo tee/etc/profile.d/maven.sh
source /etc/profile.d/maven.sh
mvn -version


7.next go to jenkins ui there under manage plugins , install maven integartion plugin,next go to tools 
there add maven like give name as maven 3.9.6, uncheck install automatically there u type /opt/apache-maven-3.9.6
clik save

8.next create a freetsyle job under this give git repo and underbuild steps
select Invoke top-level Maven targets next type maven version as Maven 3.9.6 and goals as clean install and save

9.next run the build, there it will show you the jar file creation

10. to check our jar file
sudo su - jenkins
cd /var/lib/jenkins/.m2/repository/com/mycompany/app/my-app/1.0-SNAPSHOT/

11.to see the outcome of jar file
java -jar my-app-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar
